```
 class Solution:
    def canJump(self, nums):
        """
        :type nums: List[int]
        :rtype: bool
        """
        # In general two cases arise when  we cannot reach the last index
        # 1) we overshoot as we can jump too far 2) we do not have enough jumping power to get there
        # 1) is not a possibility here as we can simply choose to jump less and get there
        # so we just have to check for 2)
        jumpingPower = 0
        for idx in range(len(nums)):
            # we reached an index that's beyond the furthest we can reach
            # this is 2) we break out
            if idx > jumpingPower: break
            # update how far we can jump
            jumpingPower = max(nums[idx]+idx,jumpingPower)
        return jumpingPower >= len(nums)-1 
```

