# Intuition
we will maintain 2 stack , 1st one(named s1 ) will having normal values but 2nd one (min_st)having always minimum value on it's top.

# Approach
1. push and pop operation will be always for 1st one stack(s1).
2. push and pop operation will be done for 2nd one stack in below cases:

   **a). if 2nd one stack is empty or value which is going to be push in 2nd stack is <= top of 2nd stack**
    **b). if both stack's top element is equal to each-other then top element is also pop from 2nd one stack.**

 **NOTE: push and pop operation will be always for 1st stack(s1)**

**minimum element will be always having 2nd one stack(min_st.top)*

           **🔥Kindly upvote if you find this helpful🔥**

# Complexity
**Time complexity:
   O(1)**
# Space Complexity 
  **O(N)**


# Code
```
