# Intuition
The intuition is to maintain maps, for
- tweets, key will be userID, and will be mapped to a pair containing time, the time when the tweet was made, and tweetID
- following, key will be the userID, and value will be a vector containing the followees the user follows
- In getNewsFeed we use a priority queue, maxheap, of the tweets by the user or his followers, we do this using 2 loops 
1 on his tweets, other one on the tweets of users he follows
and then get the tweets, all tweets if <10, or latest 10 tweets.

# Approach
MaxHeap, priority queue
unordered_maps

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n^2), for getNewsFeed, as we iterate all the tweets of all the followees

- Space complexity:
O(n)

Hope it helps!

