# Details:-
- The hashmap "following" contains all the userId that are followed by the particular userId.
- The hashmap "followers" contains all the userId that follows the particular userId.
- The hashmap "mp" contains the linkedlist of pair<Integer,Integer> type and in every pair i am storing the tweetId and the UserId.
- The hashmap "time" stores the tweetId and time.
- The hashmap "time2" stores the time and tweetId.
- The count variable basically is used to store at which time the tweet is posted.
- The count variable increases each time whenever an tweet is posted and this count variable is to check which tweetId comes first and which tweetId comes second and so on.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(N)

