Use of lower bound to find the closet element

# Approach
first sort the size array so that we can apply the lower bound on it.

Now start traversing the g array and at the same time check the lower bound of same element in the s array.
    If you find the element make Count++ and same time remove the used element from the s array, so that we avoid using duplicate.

