**IDEA** - give the largest cookie to the most greedy only if it makes him content (else why waste it ;) . So either we end up giving that cookie to the most greedy child, so `content++` and `cookie--` or otherwise we move to the next child without consuming that cookie, so no `cookie--`.
```
public int findContentChildren(int[] g, int[] s) {
        Arrays.sort(g);
        Arrays.sort(s);
        int content=0;
        int child = g.length-1; // start with most greedy child
        int cookie = s.length-1; // start with largest cookie
        for( ; child>=0 && cookie>=0 ; child--){
            if(s[cookie]>=g[child]){ // if cookie satisfies child, then only give it
                content++;
                cookie--;
            }
        }
        return content;
}
