solutions.content:
## Idea
Sort ```g``` and ```s``` in ascending order. Start with the child that needs smallest cookie and give the smallest cookie at specific time, because bigger cookie have more chances to satisfy the next child with more greediness. We greedily take this strategy until there is no candies left or all children have one cookie. 

## Implemetation
```
public class Solution {
    public int FindContentChildren(int[] g, int[] s) {

        if(s == null || s.Length == 0)
            return 0;

        Array.Sort(g);
        Array.Sort(s);

        int i = 0;

        for(int j = 0; j < s.Length && i < g.Length; j++)
        {
            if(s[j] >= g[i])
            {
                i++;
            }
        }

        return i;
    }
}
```

## Complexity
* Time: O(NlogN) where N is the sum of number of children and number of candies.
* Space: O(1)

